President Biden delivered a speech at McHenry County College in Crystal Lake, Illinois, outlining his plans for investing in both physical and human infrastructure. He emphasized the need to rebuild and modernize American infrastructure, including roads, bridges, and water systems, in order to create millions of good-paying jobs. He also highlighted the importance of investing in education, proposing to provide two years of universal preschool and two years of free community college. Additionally, President Biden discussed the need for affordable childcare, paid family leave, and expanded access to healthcare. He emphasized the urgency of addressing climate change and outlined plans to transition to clean energy and improve resilience against extreme weather events. To fund these investments, he proposed closing corporate tax loopholes, increasing taxes on the wealthy, and ending tax breaks for fossil fuel companies. President Biden concluded by emphasizing the importance of these investments in building a stronger, more equitable future for America.